Package edu.ncsu.csc216.app_manager.model.manager

Class AppManager

java.lang.Object
edu.ncsu.csc216.app_manager.model.manager.AppManager
public class AppManager extends Object
Controls the creation and modification of AppLists. Implements the Singleton pattern, works with files that contain saved Applications by calling AppReader and AppWriter classes. Provides information to GUI through methods.
Author:
Christine Weld

    • getAppListAsArray

      public Object[][] getAppListAsArray()
      Returns a 2D Object array of a list of applications that is used to populate in the GUI. The array stores rows invalid input: '&' columns, with 1 row for every Application and 4 columns (id, state, type, summary).
      Returns:
      2D object array of a list of applications

    • getAppListAsArrayByAppType

      public Object[][] getAppListAsArrayByAppType(String appType)
      Returns a 2D Object array of a list of applications filtered by type that is used to populate in the GUI. The array stores rows invalid input: '&' columns, with 1 row for every Application and 4 columns (id, state, type, summary).
      Parameters:
      appType - application type to be filtered
      Returns:
      2D object array of a list of applications filtered by type
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if given appType is null
